rs, especially of their differential rotation, which turns out\nto be strong at the core-envelope interface. They also offer more accurate\nmodels for interpreting the interferometric and spectroscopic data of\nearly-type stars.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 4 Dec 2012 16:16:56 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 19 Mar 2013 13:03:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-12"}
